dct_title_s: Subdivision of Part of the parish of Corindhap and Extension of the Suburbs of Rokewood
dct_description_sm: Lithographed by R. Meikle ; George Aitchison.
Bar scale of chains, compass rose.
Shows cemetery, land divisions, roads, drainage.
Textual descriptions of topography, such as "Quartz cropping out of places."

"Note! -- All the corners of the Allotments are marked by trenches 25 links long. The numbers of the Allotments are cut out in the turf at the corners, and the boundaries are marked by a stake, and trench 25 links long, at intervals of every ten chains."
